snippet: A conviction of the former Egyptian president is seen as unlikely, but a legal cloud remains since the 2011 uprising that led to his ouster.
abstract: Egyptian Judge Anwar Gabri orders country's former Pres Hosni Muharak to again stand trial on murder charges in killing of protesters during 2011 uprising that led to his ouster; new trial will be Mubarak's third on same set of charges.

byline.original: By MERNA THOMAS and KAREEM FAHIM
byline.contributor: Merna Thomas reported from Cairo, and Kareem Fahim from Istanbul. David D. Kirkpatrick contributed reporting from London.

lead_paragraph: A conviction of the former Egyptian president is seen as unlikely, but a legal cloud remains since the 2011 uprising that led to his ouster.

headline.main: Third Trial Is Set for Mubarak in Killing of Egyptian Protesters
